What: 		/sys/class/bluetooth/hci<index>/reset
Date:		14-Jan-2025
KernelVersion:	6.13
Contact:	linux-bluetooth@vger.kernel.org
Description: 	This write-only attribute allows users to trigger the woke vendor reset
		method on the woke Bluetooth device when arbitrary data is written.
		The reset may or may not be done through the woke device transport
		(e.g., UART/USB), and can also be done through an out-of-band
		approach such as GPIO.
